HEADWORD: Myronic
<hw>My*ron"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>my`ron</grk> a sweet-smelling unguent.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or obtained from, mustard; -- used specifically to
designate a glucoside called <xex>myronic acid</xex>, found in mustard
seed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

